<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span4">
		<h2>Code</h2>
		<p>Use {{ site_name }} to code faster and easier. It's completely web-based, so you can start coding right from the beginning, no installations required. It also gives you access to a variety of developer tools, which enable you to write more viewable code with less bugs, and find the documentation you need to develop your sketches easier.
		<p><a class="btn" href="{{ path('AceMiscBundle_about') }}">View details &raquo;</a></p>
	</div><!--/span-->
	<div class="span4">
		<h2>Compile</h2>
		<p>With {{ site_name }}, your code is compiled on the cloud, which improves compilation time and saves you the hassle of downloading, installing, and updating all the necessary tools to compile. No need to update and manage incompatible library versions either! {{site_name}} also helps you eliminate bugs faster by providing improved error reporting!</p>
		<p><a class="btn" href="{{ path('AceMiscBundle_about') }}">View details &raquo;</a></p>
	</div><!--/span-->
	<div class="span4">
		<h2>Upload</h2>
		<p>Uploading (aka flashing) your program on the Arduino has never been easier. When you are done coding, you can program your Arduino straight from your browser.<a href="javascript:void()" rel="tooltip" data-original-title="If you are using the Arduino Duemilanove, you'll need the FTDI drivers. If you are using the Arduino Uno, you're already set to go in Mac OS X and Linux, and you will only need to install drivers for Windows">No installations required*</a>. But it gets better. With {{site_name}}, you will soon be able to program your Arduino &amp; Ethernet remotely, from anywhere in the world, straight from {{site_name}}.</p>
		<p><a class="btn" href="{{ path('AceMiscBundle_about') }}">View details &raquo;</a></p>
	</div><!--/span-->
</div><!--/row-->


